page.title: 04ECOLOGY
page.content: IN THE{LUTHRIE}AND{MOONZIE}AREA THERE ARE{CROWS,ROOKS,JACKDAWS,HERONS, {SPARROWS,FINCHES,TITS AND SPARROW {HAWKS. WE HAVE MANY WOODED AREAS,WITH MIXED TYPES OF TREES.THE WEATHER IS MOSTLY DULL IN{AUTUMN,}VERY COLD IN{WINTER, WARM IN{SPRING}AND QUITE HOT IN{SUMMER EXCEPT WHEN IT RAINS. IT IS A{FARMING AREA. IN THE AREA THERE ARE{HILLS,GRASS}AND {SCRUB}WHICH PROVIDES AN ENVIRONMENT FOR NUMBERS OF ANIMALS,SUCH AS{MICE, {VOLES,RABBITS,STOATS,WEASEL,HARES, {FOXES}AND{DEER.}IN THIS AREA THERE ARE MANY DIFFERENT{TREES}SUCH AS{SCOTS {PINE,ELDER,SYCAMORE,HORSE CHESTNUT,ELM {AND OAK.}IN THE AREA THERE ARE QUITE A LOT OF INSECTS.THERE ARE{BUTTERFLIES, {MOTHS,HOUSE FLIES,BLUE BOTTLES,WOOD {LICE,BEES,WASPS,MIDGES,LADYBIRDS}AND {BEETLES.
